    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-18T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-18T05:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114A/251</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-18T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 3.36 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. [From <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>]:</p>
                <p>Commission desires to insert the following article in proposed agreement:
                    “Officer prisoners of war shall be paid in advance as soon as possible after
                    capture for the remainder [of the current] month and thereafter on the first day
                    of each calendar month.”</p>
                <p>In view of the fact that such payments are to be reimbursed to the captor state,
                    commission requests to be instructed as to whether its adoption would violate
                    any existing statute. <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Garrett</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
